channel.title: Weird Compile Error
channel.description:
Everytime I run my server, on PvPscape, it keeps giving me this error: [img]http://img409.imageshack.us/img409/3342/errorbg7.png[/img]
Heres the code in the compiler: [code]@echo off title Compiling... color f0 echo ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- echo / \ echo / Now compiling server... \ echo / \ echo ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- "%ProgramFiles%\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -g:none -nowarn -d ./Class/ ./Java/*.java
title PvpScape color f0 echo ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- echo / \ echo / Now starting server... \ echo / \ echo ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- set java="C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\java.exe" java -Xmx1024m -cp .;./Class; server pause[/code]
Thanks![br][size=1]Posted on: January 12, 2007, 10:35:24 PM[/size][hr]Bump

item.title: Weird Compile Error
item.dc:creator: @lothy Lothy
item.description:
@lothy wrote:

ritacame:

All I did was rename all the pvpscape names in client.java to FableScape, then I compiled and got that error. I am using jdk 1.6.0_01

Can’t just do that. I’m guessing you may have renamed certain things that can’t be renamed so easily. (For example, integers or booleans that I may have declared).

I’d suggest you start again, only this time be more careful. There’s only a few places you need to change PvpScape, so find and replace them manually.
